10/16/84  kermit request: send, s

Syntax: s local_source_path {remote_destination_path}


Function: Sends the file or files specified by local_source_path to the
microcomputer.


Arguments:
local_source_path
   Is the pathname of the file to be sent to the remote.  The star
   convention is allowed.
remote_destination_path
   is the pathname under which the transmitted file will be stored on
   the remote.


Notes:
   If remote_destination_path is specified when sending a file group
   to the microcomputer, the first file received will be stored under
   the given path, and the remainder will be stored under their own
   names.
